.TH "vfs_fsync_range" 9 "vfs_fsync_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_fsync_range \- helper to sync a range of data & metadata to disk
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vfs_fsync_range
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "loff_t start "  ","
.BI "loff_t end "  ","
.BI "int datasync "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
file to sync
.IP "start" 12
offset in bytes of the beginning of data range to sync
.IP "end" 12
offset in bytes of the end of data range (inclusive)
.IP "datasync" 12
perform only datasync
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write back data in range \fIstart\fP..\fIend\fP and metadata for \fIfile\fP to disk.  If
\fIdatasync\fP is set only metadata needed to access modified file data is
written.
